name: Fayzur Rahman
content:
Fayzur Rahman Bengali: (ফয়জুর রহমান) is a Bangladesh Awami League politician and the incumbent Member of Parliament from Brahmanbaria-5.[1]
 Rahman was born on 5 November 1966. He has studied up to SSC or grade ten.[2]
 In 1992 Rahman joined Epic Design, a buying house, as an assistant merchandiser. In 1995 he joined the merchandising department of the Winners Limited, a buying house, as a manager. He was appointed the managing director of Tusuka garments.[3] He was elected to parliament from Brahmanbaria-5 in 2008 as a candidate of Bangladesh Awami League. He is the Chairman of Novoair.[4]

Fayzur Rahman Bengali: (ফয়জুর রহমান) is a Bangladesh Awami League politician and the incumbent Member of Parliament from Brahmanbaria-5.[1]

Early life[edit]
Rahman was born on 5 November 1966. He has studied up to SSC or grade ten.[2]

Career[edit]
In 1992 Rahman joined Epic Design, a buying house, as an assistant merchandiser. In 1995 he joined the merchandising department of the Winners Limited, a buying house, as a manager. He was appointed the managing director of Tusuka garments.[3] He was elected to parliament from Brahmanbaria-5 in 2008 as a candidate of Bangladesh Awami League. He is the Chairman of Novoair.[4]
